<opener><address><addrLine>From the Governor,</addrLine>
<addrLine>H.M.Prison, Mountjoy, Dublin.</address>
<dateline><date>2<hi rend="superscript">nd.</hi> February, 1916</date></dateline>
<address>To Mrs.Mabel Fitzgerald, 2 Loretto Villas, Bray.</addrLine></address></opener>
<p>With reference to your letter of 1<hi rend="superscript">st.</hi> instant, I have to inform you that you
<lb/> will be entitled to visit your husband on Saturday next, the 5<hi rend="superscript">th.</hi> inst., and that
<lb/> the period of the visit may <sic>extendto</sic> half an hour. Your husband states he
<lb/> would like to see <gap/> Einar O'Duffy, or one of his friends.</p>
<p>A baby in arms does not count as a visitor. If possible, it would be more
<lb/> convenient for the visit to take place in the forenoon, but if Saturday is an
<lb/> inconvenient <add>day,</add> I may mention that your husband states Monday would be an equally
<lb/> suitable day for him <add>arriving</add>.</p>
<signed>C.T.Munro</signed>
Governor.
        
    

    
                </body>
            </text>

        
            
        

         

